.cli
  %h1 CLI
  %h2 What is it?
  %p
    The Gobot CLI is a command line interface that provides several generators 
    to help you get started writing your own Gobot Adaptors and Drivers.
  %h2 How to install
  :markdown
        :::bash
        go get -u github.com/hybridgroup/gobot/gobot


  %h2 How can I use it?
  %p
    :markdown
      The Gobot CLI tools are easy to use, designed to be intuitive, and offer 
      contextual help regarding the commands you're using. Once you have the 
      `gobot` cli installed, the toolkit will be available at all times. 
      To find all available commands, just run `gobot help`.

  %h3 Printing a list of available commands
  :markdown
        :::bash
        NAME:
           gobot - Command Line Utility for Gobot

        USAGE:
           gobot [global options] command [command options] [arguments...]

        VERSION:
           0.1

        COMMANDS:
           generate     Generate new Gobot skeleton project
           help, h      Shows a list of commands or help for one command
           
        GLOBAL OPTIONS:
           --help, -h           show help
           --version, -v        print the version


  %h2 What Gobot CLI commands are available?
  %p
    If you have only installed gobot, the list of available commands is the one printed in the section above, let's review them one by one.

  %h3 gobot generate [name]
  %h5 Description
  %p Generates a new Gobot component or adaptor module.
  :markdown
        :::bash
        gobot generate test
        Creating /private/tmp/gobot-test
        Creating /private/tmp/gobot-test/test_adaptor.go
        Creating /private/tmp/gobot-test/test_driver.go
        Creating /private/tmp/gobot-test/README.md
        Creating /private/tmp/gobot-test/LICENSE
        Creating /private/tmp/gobot-test/test_driver_test.go
        Creating /private/tmp/gobot-test/test_adaptor_test.go
        Creating /private/tmp/gobot-test/gobot-test_suite_test.go
